%% Diagram: Loading a board with its pins - colocation collapses most reads to one shard, the tail fans out in parallel
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as Application
    participant Cache as Memcache / Redis
    participant DB1 as MySQL shard 3429 (board's home)
    participant DB2 as MySQL shard 4172 (repinned pin)
    participant DB3 as MySQL shard 5018 (repinned pin)

    App->>Cache: GET board:<board_id>
    Cache-->>App: miss
    App->>DB1: SELECT data FROM boards WHERE local_id = ...
    DB1-->>App: board JSON

    App->>Cache: GET board_has_pins:<board_id>
    Cache-->>App: miss
    App->>DB1: SELECT pin_id FROM board_has_pins ORDER BY sequence DESC LIMIT 50
    DB1-->>App: 50 pin_ids

    par parallel batch read per shard
        App->>DB1: SELECT data FROM pins WHERE local_id IN (... colocated 48 ids ...)
    and
        App->>DB2: SELECT data FROM pins WHERE local_id IN (... 1 id ...)
    and
        App->>DB3: SELECT data FROM pins WHERE local_id IN (... 1 id ...)
    end

    DB1-->>App: 48 pin blobs
    DB2-->>App: 1 pin blob
    DB3-->>App: 1 pin blob

    Note over App: Wall-clock latency = slowest single shard query
